# RUDIS Documentation - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is the RUDIS technical documentation repository - comprehensive documentation for the RUDIS Shopify Plus eCommerce platform. The documentation follows Arcadia Digital's ARCDIG-DOCS methodology and provides evidence-based technical documentation for multiple audiences: developers, operations teams, business users, and AI assistants.

## Core Principles

### Business-First Approach
- Write for business users, not just developers
- Balance technical accuracy with business clarity
- Use progressive disclosure (high-level → details)
- Organize around use cases and workflows
- Avoid unnecessary technical jargon

### Evidence-Based Documentation
- Base documentation on actual codebase analysis
- Document only integrations with theme code evidence
- Verify all documentation against source material
- Use real data exports, not assumptions
- Preserve investigation patterns and failure examples

### Multi-Audience Support
- Different documentation for different audiences (AI agents, developers, operations, business users)
- Static memory file README for comprehensive context
- Clear navigation for all user types
- Role-based training and handoff documentation

### Client Ownership
- Design for seamless handoff
- Client-specific repositories
- Easy maintenance and updates
- Long-term sustainability

